Lin was instrumental in "interpreting" Mao's "thought" during the cultural revolution, for example, which ended with the deaths of hundreds of thousands of Chinese and did lasting damage to Chinese society. And Tan Zhenlin, another suspicious character among Mao's advisors, tried to convince Mao everything was fine while millions of Chinese were starving to death due to his policies:


https://books.google.com/books?id=9pPxwn6EvR4C&pg=PA142
